title: |md
  # UPDATE_TAG Flow — UID-Only / TigerTag / OpenSpool
  Tags without writable weight fields
|

direction: down

User: {shape: person}
Scanner: Scanner
Middleware: Middleware
Klipper: Klipper
Moonraker: Moonraker
Spoolman: {shape: cylinder}

Legend: {
  near: top-right
  style.fill: "#FAFAFA"
  style.stroke: "#CCCCCC"

  s1: " " {style.fill: "#2E86C1"; width: 12; height: 12}
  l1: Sending data
  s1 -> l1: {style.stroke: "#2E86C1"; style.stroke-width: 2}

  s2: " " {style.fill: "#27AE60"; width: 12; height: 12}
  l2: Fetching data
  s2 -> l2: {style.stroke: "#27AE60"; style.stroke-width: 2}

  s3: " " {style.fill: "#333333"; width: 12; height: 12}
  l3: User action / internal
  s3 -> l3: {style.stroke: "#333333"; style.stroke-width: 2}
}

# --- Initial Scan ---
User -> Scanner: 1. Scan spool tag (UID only) {
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}
Scanner -> Middleware: 2. MQTT tag/state\n(uid, no weight data) {
  style.stroke: "#2E86C1"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}
Middleware -> Spoolman: 3. Lookup spool by NFC UID {
  style.stroke: "#27AE60"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

User -> Klipper: 4. Print one or more jobs {
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Moonraker handles tracking ---
Moonraker -> Spoolman: 5. Moonraker syncs filament\nusage in real-time\n(sync_rate in moonraker.conf) {
  style.stroke: "#2E86C1"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- PRINT_END fires UPDATE_TAG ---
Klipper -> Klipper: 6. PRINT_END fires\nUPDATE_TAG macro runs {
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}
Klipper -> Moonraker: 7. SET_GCODE_VARIABLE\npending=1 {
  style.stroke: "#2E86C1"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}
Moonraker -> Middleware: 8. Websocket push {
  style.stroke: "#2E86C1"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- No-op ---
no_op: No action taken {
  style.fill: "#FADBD8"

  reason1: Tag has no writable weight field
  reason2: Moonraker already syncs\nusage to Spoolman
  result: UPDATE_TAG is a no-op\nfor this tag type

  reason1 -> result
  reason2 -> result
}

Middleware -> no_op: 9. Middleware detects\nUID-only tag — skip {
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}
